summary: I read the books after the first season and one of the few things that stood out for me, outside of the Red Wedding (that's a...
body:
I read the books after the first season and one of the few things that stood out for me, outside of the Red Wedding (that’s a whole other story) is GRRM Petyr Baelish/ Olenna Tyrell and the death of Joffrey.

When I was reading it and it was uncovered to be Littlefinger pulling the strings behind the scenes it was like someone had socked me in the face, it was that jaw dropping the reveal and I consider myself to read between the lines and have a couple suitable theories stashed away for a rainy day.

Cut to the present, GOT’s Baelish, and he’s just so fucking gross and oily with none of that sly machinations behind the scenes, this Baelish announces his intentions with ill disguised eyebrow quirks, a smug face and an everchanging accent. Literally everytime he’s in Sansa presence I cringe so much because his very character is someone whose on the prowl for a Catelyn 2.0.

I got abit carried away there, but my main point was I had such high hopes for this scene but a book is a different medium to a film and can’t carry the gravitas of personal POVs chapters, but it can give words flesh and blood to breathe life into them and connect all the small details together.

I still loathe Petyr Baelish though.
